A renowned drummer for The Tonight Show has died at the age of 84 after suffering a heart attack at his California home.

Ed Shaughnessy performed with Doc Severinsen's Tonight Show band for close to 30 years and became a central figure on the popular TV programme.

He was well-known for his drum battles against frequent guest Buddy Rich and even played with Jimi Hendrix on the show.

