Shaughnessy also played the drums for performances by Aretha Franklin, James Brown, Johnny Cash and Merle Haggard on the show.

A close friend of the musician, Robyn Flans said Shaughnessy suffered a fatal heart attack at his home in Calabasas, California, on Friday morning.

Flans, who co-wrote Shaughnessy's autobiography 'Lucky Drummer', told RollingStone.com: 'Every drummer has his story to tell of how kind and generous of spirit he was.

'He influenced so many people. He was the guy. He was on television every night reaching all those people. You always saw the smile behind the kit. That was my Eddie.'

